---+Easy Timeline Plugin 
This plugin allows one to use the &lt;easytimeline> tags to generate a timeline on the fly.  Just like the &lt;timeline> plugin for [[http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/EasyTimeline][MediaWiki]] which I based this plugin on.

Note: I based much of this code on the [[http://TWiki.org/cgi-bin/view/Plugins/RecursiveRenderPlugin][RecursiveRenderPlugin]] so many thanks to it's author for something to learn how to code a twiki plugin from.

---++ <nop>%TOPIC%  Syntax
Simply &lt;easytimeline>
Easytimeline input data
&lt;/easytimeline>

---++ <nop>%TOPIC% Known Issues
   * Since the image uses the topic name, only one timeline per topic possible at this time.
   * I made a slight patch to !EasyTimeline.pl as it seems to have a bug where it doesn't actually write out the .map file by default.  You can get the patch diff file [[http://www.miguelito.org/EasyTimeline.pl.diff][off my site]].
   * I did a lot of checking for issues like binaries where they're expected, ability to write where needed, etc.. but I didn't deal with ploticus failing other then the output files not being there (or readable) when we get to that state.
d4 807
a810 1
---++ <nop>%TOPIC% Global Settings
d814 2
a815 2
	* One line description, shown in the %TWIKIWEB%.TextFormattingRules topic:
		* Set SHORTDESCRIPTION = This plugin adds =&lt;easytimeline&gt;= tags
d817 2
a818 10
	* Debug plugin: (See output in =data/debug.txt=)
		* Set DEBUG = 0
		* Set TMPBASE = /tmp
		* Set EASYTIMELINESCRIPT = /usr/local/bin/EasyTimeline.pl
		* Set IMAGEDIR = /home/httpd/html/twiki/timelines
		* Set URLDIR   = /twiki/timelines
		* Set PERLBIN  = /usr/bin/perl
		* Set PLBIN = /usr/bin/pl
		* Set TWIKIVIEWURL = /twiki/bin/view
		* Set PICFORMAT = png
